  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery boys look for when I exchange my old washing machine for a new one?",
  "response": "When you exchange your old washing machine for a new one on Flipkart, the delivery personnel or \"delivery boys\" typically look for a few key things to ensure a smooth and successful exchange process:\n\n1. **Condition of the Old Washing Machine**:  \n   - They will inspect the old washing machine to ensure it matches the description you provided during the exchange process.  \n   - The machine should be in working or repairable condition unless Flipkart explicitly states otherwise.\n\n2. **Completeness of the Old Appliance**:  \n   - They will check if all essential parts (e.g., drum, knobs, panels, etc.) are intact and included.  \n   - Missing or severely damaged components might affect the exchange value or eligibility.\n\n3. **Cleanliness**:  \n   - The washing machine should be reasonably clean and free from excessive dirt or debris.  \n\n4. **Proof of Ownership**:  \n   - You may need to provide proof that the old washing machine belongs to you, such as a receipt or any other relevant documentation.\n\n5. **Eligibility for Exchange**:  \n   - They will verify that the old washing machine meets Flipkart's exchange criteria, which are usually outlined during the purchase process.\n\n6. **Pickup Documentation**:  \n   - The delivery personnel will provide you with a receipt or acknowledgment of the pickup, confirming that the old appliance has been collected.\n\n### Tips for a Smooth Exchange:\n- Ensure the old washing machine is uninstalled and ready for pickup.  \n- Clean the appliance before the delivery team arrives.  \n- Keep any necessary documents ready, such as proof of purchase or the exchange voucher provided by Flipkart.  \n\nIf there are any discrepancies or issues with the old washing machine, the delivery personnel might refuse the exchange or adjust the value offered. It\u2019s always a good idea to double-check Flipkart\u2019s exchange policy beforehand.",
